src=3D"GameConcepts_Blockades_files/image002.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D12=
 v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_3"><![endif]><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>When trade sanctions exist b=
etween
two empires, blockades may be declared against enemy colonies and space por=
ts. In
this situation no trade by any empire is permitted with the blockaded colon=
y or
base.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>E=
nforcement
of a blockade is usually accomplished by a fleet of ships from the empire
initiating the blockade. These ships will attack any ship that attempts to =
run
the blockade.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>A=
 blockade
is indicated in the main view by a dashed orange circle around the blockaded
base or colony.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>B=
lockades
last until the initiator cancels them, or until the trade sanctions between=
 the
two empires are lifted.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Initiating and can=
celling
Blockades<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_4" o:s=
pid=3D"_x0000_s1026"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:58.85pt;margin=
-top:0;
 width:110.05pt;height:109.6pt;z-index:251658240;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"GameConcepts_Blockades_files/image003.png" o:title=3D"=
"/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D147 height=3D146
src=3D"GameConcepts_Blockades_files/image004.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D12=
 v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_4"><![endif]><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>To initiate a blockade again=
st
another empire, select one of your military ships or one of your fleets and
assign a blockade mission against a particular colony or base. The blockade
begins when your ships arrive to enforce the blockade. Note that if you
blockade a colony, any space port at the colony is also automatically
blockaded.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>T=
o cancel a
blockade you have initiated, simply assign a new mission to your ship or fl=
eet
that is implementing the blockade.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Y=
ou will be
notified if another empire initiates a blockade against you. You will also =
be
notified when the blockade ends. When you select a blockaded colony or base=
 the
Selection Panel will also contain a message describing the blockade.</span>=
</p>

